protective as those in this Agreement.\n\n4. Term and Termination. The nondisclosure provisions of this Agreement shall survive the termination of this Agreement and Recipient's duty to hold Confidential Information in confidence shall remain in effect until the Confidential Information no longer qualifies as a trade secret or until Disclosing Party sends Recipient written notice releasing Recipient from this Agreement, whichever occurs first.\n\n5. Remedies. Recipient acknowledges that any breach of this Agreement may cause irreparable harm to the Disclosing Party for which monetary damages would be inadequate, and the Disclosing Party shall be entitled to seek injunctive relief in addition to any other available remedies.\"",
